{"repo": "fla-org/flash-linear-attention", "pull_number": 627, "instance_id": "fla-org__flash-linear-attention-627", "issue_numbers": [625], "base_commit": "f0de028bf3a4a6bb7c39f9c9585c4f03a7b72641", "patch": "diff --git a/fla/modules/convolution.py b/fla/modules/convolution.py\nindex 1c26a07edb..329d236ea3 100644\n--- a/fla/modules/convolution.py\n+++ b/fla/modules/convolution.py\n@@ -398,6 +398,7 @@ def causal_conv1d_update_kernel(\n         tl.store(p_cache, b_cache, boundary_check=(0, 1))\n \n \n+@input_guard\n def causal_conv1d_fwd(\n     x: torch.Tensor,\n     weight: torch.Tensor,\n", "test_patch": "", "problem_statement": "[Bug] Kimi LInear crashing at fla.kda.gate + Triton\n### Checklist\n\n- [x] I have checked [FAQs](https://github.com/fla-org/flash-linear-attention/blob/main/FAQs.md) and existing issues for similar problems\n- [x] Please report this bug in English to ensure wider understanding and support\n\n### Describe the Bug\n\nNot sure if this is Kimi modeling bug or something to do with fla.  It crashes during inference. \n\n<img width=\"1200\" height=\"872\" alt=\"Image\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/b00bdaad-173c-456a-8c0a-8dc7df9ab0b0\" />\n\n<img width=\"1698\" height=\"2050\" alt=\"Image\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/07c7762f-1c68-409b-9f40-55c11d4cbddc\" />\n\n\n### Steps to Reproduce the Bug\n\nRun Kimi Linear model on HF with Nvidia A100\n\n### Expected Behavior\n\nNot crash.\n\n### Environment Information\n\n1. Torch: 2.9.0+cu130\n2. Triton: 3.5.0\n\nInstsalled flash linear via:\n\n```\n# uninstall both packages first to ensure a successful upgrade\npip uninstall fla-core flash-linear-attention -y && pip install -U git+https://github.com/fla-org/flash-linear-attention\n```\n\n", "hints_text": "Have you tried with `export CUDA_LAUNCH_BLOCKING=1`?   I will check this out. Since our CI only have H100.\n@zhiyuan1i  Here is the stacktrace with `CUDA_LAUNCH_BLOCKING=1`\n\n```py\n           ^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^\n../.cache/huggingface/modules/transformers_modules/Kimi_hyphen_Linear_hyphen_48B_hyphen_A3B_hyphen_Instruct/modeling_kimi.py:778: in forward\n    hidden_states = self.self_attn(\n../vm313t/lib/python3.13t/site-packages/torch/nn/modules/module.py:1775: in _wrapped_call_impl\n    return self._call_impl(*args, **kwargs)\n           ^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^\n../vm313t/lib/python3.13t/site-packages/torch/nn/modules/module.py:1786: in _call_impl\n    return forward_call(*args, **kwargs)\n           ^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^\n../.cache/huggingface/modules/transformers_modules/Kimi_hyphen_Linear_hyphen_48B_hyphen_A3B_hyphen_Instruct/modeling_kimi.py:465: in forward\n    q, conv_state_q = self.q_conv1d(\n../vm313t/lib/python3.13t/site-packages/torch/nn/modules/module.py:1775: in _wrapped_call_impl\n    return self._call_impl(*args, **kwargs)\n           ^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^\n../vm313t/lib/python3.13t/site-packages/torch/nn/modules/module.py:1786: in _call_impl\n    return forward_call(*args, **kwargs)\n           ^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^\n../vm313t/lib/python3.13t/site-packages/torch/utils/_contextlib.py:120: in decorate_context\n    return func(*args, **kwargs)\n           ^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^\ngptqmodel/nn_modules/hooked_linear.py:334: in forward\n    output = _call_wrapped_forward(self._forward_source, super().forward, x, args, kwargs)\n             ^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^\ngptqmodel/nn_modules/hooked_linear.py:196: in _call_wrapped_forward\n    return _call_module_with_optional_args(wrapped_module, input_tensor, args, kwargs)\n           ^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^\ngptqmodel/nn_modules/hooked_linear.py:172: in _call_module_with_optional_args\n    return module(input_tensor, *args, **kwargs)\n           ^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^\n../vm313t/lib/python3.13t/site-packages/torch/nn/modules/module.py:1775: in _wrapped_call_impl\n    return self._call_impl(*args, **kwargs)\n           ^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^\n../vm313t/lib/python3.13t/site-packages/torch/nn/modules/module.py:1786: in _call_impl\n    return forward_call(*args, **kwargs)\n           ^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^\n../vm313t/lib/python3.13t/site-packages/fla/modules/convolution.py:953: in forward\n    return causal_conv1d(\n../vm313t/lib/python3.13t/site-packages/fla/utils.py:164: in wrapper\n    return fn(*contiguous_args, **contiguous_kwargs)\n           ^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^\n../vm313t/lib/python3.13t/site-packages/fla/modules/convolution.py:733: in causal_conv1d\n    y, final_state = CausalConv1dFunction.apply(\n../vm313t/lib/python3.13t/site-packages/torch/autograd/function.py:581: in apply\n    return super().apply(*args, **kwargs)  # type: ignore[misc]\n           ^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^\n../vm313t/lib/python3.13t/site-packages/fla/utils.py:164: in wrapper\n    return fn(*contiguous_args, **contiguous_kwargs)\n           ^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^\n../vm313t/lib/python3.13t/site-packages/fla/modules/convolution.py:654: in forward\n    y, final_state = causal_conv1d_fwd(\n../vm313t/lib/python3.13t/site-packages/fla/modules/convolution.py:425: in causal_conv1d_fwd\n    causal_conv1d_fwd_kernel[grid](\n../vm313t/lib/python3.13t/site-packages/triton/runtime/jit.py:419: in <lambda>\n    return lambda *args, **kwargs: self.run(grid=grid, warmup=False, *args, **kwargs)\n                                   ^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^\n../vm313t/lib/python3.13t/site-packages/triton/runtime/autotuner.py:452: in run\n    return self.fn.run(*args, **kwargs)\n           ^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^\n../vm313t/lib/python3.13t/site-packages/triton/runtime/autotuner.py:250: in run\n    ret = self.fn.run(\n../vm313t/lib/python3.13t/site-packages/triton/runtime/jit.py:757: in run\n    kernel.run(grid_0, grid_1, grid_2, stream, kernel.function, kernel.packed_metadata, launch_metadata,\n_ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ \n\nself = <triton.backends.nvidia.driver.CudaLauncher object at 0x4d6cee28a10>, gridX = 32, gridY = 115, gridZ = 1, stream = 0, function = 130177155005440\nargs = ((4, 1, 512, 1, 1, 1), <triton.compiler.compiler.LazyDict object at 0x4d6f56ca030>, <triton.knobs.HookChain object at ...with `TORCH_USE_CUDA_DSA` to enable device-side assertions.\\n\") raised in repr()] Tensor object at 0x4d6eab8cf90>, ...)\nallocate_scratch = <function CudaLauncher.__call__.<locals>.allocate_scratch at 0x4d6f836b9a0>, global_scratch = None, profile_scratch = None\n\n    def __call__(self, gridX, gridY, gridZ, stream, function, *args):\n    \n        def allocate_scratch(size, align, allocator):\n            if size > 0:\n                grid_size = gridX * gridY * gridZ\n                alloc_size = grid_size * self.num_ctas * size\n                alloc_fn = allocator.get()\n                return alloc_fn(alloc_size, align, stream)\n            return None\n    \n        global_scratch = allocate_scratch(self.global_scratch_size, self.global_scratch_align, _allocation._allocator)\n        profile_scratch = allocate_scratch(self.profile_scratch_size, self.profile_scratch_align,\n                                           _allocation._profile_allocator)\n>       self.launch(gridX, gridY, gridZ, stream, function, self.launch_cooperative_grid, self.launch_pdl,\n                    global_scratch, profile_scratch, *args)\nE       RuntimeError: Triton Error [CUDA]: an illegal memory access was encountered\n\n../vm313t/lib/python3.13t/site-packages/triton/backends/nvidia/driver.py:712: RuntimeError\n```\nhey, thank you so much for reporting this bug! could you find a minimal code snippet (that is easily runnable) to reproduce this bug? we'll prioritize fixing it.\n@Qubitium Thank you for your details.  I will check if I need to add a pure pytorch code(if it's a triton bug).\n@zhiyuan1i  @sustcsonglin  I just tested Kimi-Linear on H200 vm (torch 2.9 + latest fla + cuda 13.0 + triton 3.5) and it's also crashing at the same location. I think this is may may not be a FLA bug but a Triton `autotuner` interaction with my HookLinear wrapper. I am using [gpt-qmodel](https://github.com/modelcloud/gptqmodel) to quantize kimi-linear which `wraps` the `nn.Linear` and `conv1d` inside a thin wrapper to capture `activations`.  It is a dead simple wrapper but I think it is causing something inside Triton to trigger a crash. I wil do more checks on my side. \n@Qubitium Could you provide the running cases that can reproduce the error?\n@yzhangcs  I am currently debugging both my code and `fla`.  Wll provide a unit test if I can't find fix it. \n\n", "all_hints_text": "Have you tried with `export CUDA_LAUNCH_BLOCKING=1`?   I will check this out. Since our CI only have H100.\n@zhiyuan1i  Here is the stacktrace with `CUDA_LAUNCH_BLOCKING=1`\n\n```py\n           ^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^\n../.cache/huggingface/modules/transformers_modules/Kimi_hyphen_Linear_hyphen_48B_hyphen_A3B_hyphen_Instruct/modeling_kimi.py:778: in forward\n    hidden_states = self.self_attn(\n../vm313t/lib/python3.13t/site-packages/torch/nn/modules/module.py:1775: in _wrapped_call_impl\n    return self._call_impl(*args, **kwargs)\n           ^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^\n../vm313t/lib/python3.13t/site-packages/torch/nn/modules/module.py:1786: in _call_impl\n    return forward_call(*args, **kwargs)\n           ^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^\n../.cache/huggingface/modules/transformers_modules/Kimi_hyphen_Linear_hyphen_48B_hyphen_A3B_hyphen_Instruct/modeling_kimi.py:465: in forward\n    q, conv_state_q = self.q_conv1d(\n../vm313t/lib/python3.13t/site-packages/torch/nn/modules/module.py:1775: in _wrapped_call_impl\n    return self._call_impl(*args, **kwargs)\n           ^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^\n../vm313t/lib/python3.13t/site-packages/torch/nn/modules/module.py:1786: in _call_impl\n    return forward_call(*args, **kwargs)\n           ^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^\n../vm313t/lib/python3.13t/site-packages/torch/utils/_contextlib.py:120: in decorate_context\n    return func(*args, **kwargs)\n           ^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^\ngptqmodel/nn_modules/hooked_linear.py:334: in forward\n    output = _call_wrapped_forward(self._forward_source, super().forward, x, args, kwargs)\n             ^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^\ngptqmodel/nn_modules/hooked_linear.py:196: in _call_wrapped_forward\n    return _call_module_with_optional_args(wrapped_module, input_tensor, args, kwargs)\n           ^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^\ngptqmodel/nn_modules/hooked_linear.py:172: in _call_module_with_optional_args\n    return module(input_tensor, *args, **kwargs)\n           ^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^\n../vm313t/lib/python3.13t/site-packages/torch/nn/modules/module.py:1775: in _wrapped_call_impl\n    return self._call_impl(*args, **kwargs)\n           ^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^\n../vm313t/lib/python3.13t/site-packages/torch/nn/modules/module.py:1786: in _call_impl\n    return forward_call(*args, **kwargs)\n           ^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^\n../vm313t/lib/python3.13t/site-packages/fla/modules/convolution.py:953: in forward\n    return causal_conv1d(\n../vm313t/lib/python3.13t/site-packages/fla/utils.py:164: in wrapper\n    return fn(*contiguous_args, **contiguous_kwargs)\n           ^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^\n../vm313t/lib/python3.13t/site-packages/fla/modules/convolution.py:733: in causal_conv1d\n    y, final_state = CausalConv1dFunction.apply(\n../vm313t/lib/python3.13t/site-packages/torch/autograd/function.py:581: in apply\n    return super().apply(*args, **kwargs)  # type: ignore[misc]\n           ^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^\n../vm313t/lib/python3.13t/site-packages/fla/utils.py:164: in wrapper\n    return fn(*contiguous_args, **contiguous_kwargs)\n           ^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^\n../vm313t/lib/python3.13t/site-packages/fla/modules/convolution.py:654: in forward\n    y, final_state = causal_conv1d_fwd(\n../vm313t/lib/python3.13t/site-packages/fla/modules/convolution.py:425: in causal_conv1d_fwd\n    causal_conv1d_fwd_kernel[grid](\n../vm313t/lib/python3.13t/site-packages/triton/runtime/jit.py:419: in <lambda>\n    return lambda *args, **kwargs: self.run(grid=grid, warmup=False, *args, **kwargs)\n                                   ^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^\n../vm313t/lib/python3.13t/site-packages/triton/runtime/autotuner.py:452: in run\n    return self.fn.run(*args, **kwargs)\n           ^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^\n../vm313t/lib/python3.13t/site-packages/triton/runtime/autotuner.py:250: in run\n    ret = self.fn.run(\n../vm313t/lib/python3.13t/site-packages/triton/runtime/jit.py:757: in run\n    kernel.run(grid_0, grid_1, grid_2, stream, kernel.function, kernel.packed_metadata, launch_metadata,\n_ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ \n\nself = <triton.backends.nvidia.driver.CudaLauncher object at 0x4d6cee28a10>, gridX = 32, gridY = 115, gridZ = 1, stream = 0, function = 130177155005440\nargs = ((4, 1, 512, 1, 1, 1), <triton.compiler.compiler.LazyDict object at 0x4d6f56ca030>, <triton.knobs.HookChain object at ...with `TORCH_USE_CUDA_DSA` to enable device-side assertions.\\n\") raised in repr()] Tensor object at 0x4d6eab8cf90>, ...)\nallocate_scratch = <function CudaLauncher.__call__.<locals>.allocate_scratch at 0x4d6f836b9a0>, global_scratch = None, profile_scratch = None\n\n    def __call__(self, gridX, gridY, gridZ, stream, function, *args):\n    \n        def allocate_scratch(size, align, allocator):\n            if size > 0:\n                grid_size = gridX * gridY * gridZ\n                alloc_size = grid_size * self.num_ctas * size\n                alloc_fn = allocator.get()\n                return alloc_fn(alloc_size, align, stream)\n            return None\n    \n        global_scratch = allocate_scratch(self.global_scratch_size, self.global_scratch_align, _allocation._allocator)\n        profile_scratch = allocate_scratch(self.profile_scratch_size, self.profile_scratch_align,\n                                           _allocation._profile_allocator)\n>       self.launch(gridX, gridY, gridZ, stream, function, self.launch_cooperative_grid, self.launch_pdl,\n                    global_scratch, profile_scratch, *args)\nE       RuntimeError: Triton Error [CUDA]: an illegal memory access was encountered\n\n../vm313t/lib/python3.13t/site-packages/triton/backends/nvidia/driver.py:712: RuntimeError\n```\nhey, thank you so much for reporting this bug! could you find a minimal code snippet (that is easily runnable) to reproduce this bug? we'll prioritize fixing it.\n@Qubitium Thank you for your details.  I will check if I need to add a pure pytorch code(if it's a triton bug).\n@zhiyuan1i  @sustcsonglin  I just tested Kimi-Linear on H200 vm (torch 2.9 + latest fla + cuda 13.0 + triton 3.5) and it's also crashing at the same location. I think this is may may not be a FLA bug but a Triton `autotuner` interaction with my HookLinear wrapper. I am using [gpt-qmodel](https://github.com/modelcloud/gptqmodel) to quantize kimi-linear which `wraps` the `nn.Linear` and `conv1d` inside a thin wrapper to capture `activations`.  It is a dead simple wrapper but I think it is causing something inside Triton to trigger a crash. I wil do more checks on my side. \n@Qubitium Could you provide the running cases that can reproduce the error?\n@yzhangcs  I am currently debugging both my code and `fla`.  Wll provide a unit test if I can't find fix it. \n> [@zhiyuan1i](https://github.com/zhiyuan1i) [@sustcsonglin](https://github.com/sustcsonglin) I just tested Kimi-Linear on H200 vm (torch 2.9 + latest fla + cuda 13.0 + triton 3.5) and it's also crashing at the same location. I think this is may may not be a FLA bug but a Triton `autotuner` interaction with my HookLinear wrapper. I am using [gpt-qmodel](https://github.com/modelcloud/gptqmodel) to quantize kimi-linear which `wraps` the `nn.Linear` and `conv1d` inside a thin wrapper to capture `activations`. It is a dead simple wrapper but I think it is causing something inside Triton to trigger a crash. I wil do more checks on my side.\n\nI will soon release a pure pytorch code. However, I'm not sure if the code we used for inference-only moe has some bad effects on your quantization script.\n\n", "commit_urls": ["https://github.com/fla-org/flash-linear-attention/commit/dbed6faf4e3e8eab709f4f4a47dcce0ed3833246", "https://github.com/fla-org/flash-linear-attention/commit/3b0bac0a6d1ab2c3cead87f76c0ebdd0ee23adcd", "https://github.com/fla-org/flash-linear-attention/commit/2c3d2f674d320fe157f033ec608438bdf338a4d1"], "created_at": "2025-10-31T04:23:03Z"}
{"repo": "fla-org/flash-linear-attention", "pull_number": 633, "instance_id": "fla-org__flash-linear-attention-633", "issue_numbers": [632], "base_commit": "db55f885dad4badb82f9d72430b523e07a0a73cd", "patch": "diff --git a/fla/ops/path_attn/parallel_path_bwd_inter_dkv.py b/fla/ops/path_attn/parallel_path_bwd_inter_dkv.py\nindex 56882980da..1806263eb2 100644\n--- a/fla/ops/path_attn/parallel_path_bwd_inter_dkv.py\n+++ b/fla/ops/path_attn/parallel_path_bwd_inter_dkv.py\n@@ -77,7 +77,7 @@ def parallel_path_bwd_dkv_kernel(\n     # load query\n     p_k = tl.make_block_ptr(k, (T, K), (H*K, 1), (i_t * BT, 0), (BT, BK), (1, 0))\n     b_k = tl.load(p_k, boundary_check=(0, 1))\n-    p_v = tl.make_block_ptr(v, (T, K), (H*K, 1), (i_t * BT, 0), (BT, BK), (1, 0))\n+    p_v = tl.make_block_ptr(v, (T, V), (H*V, 1), (i_t * BT, 0), (BT, BV), (1, 0))\n     b_v = tl.load(p_v, boundary_check=(0, 1))\n \n     if USE_GATE:\n@@ -90,7 +90,7 @@ def parallel_path_bwd_dkv_kernel(\n         b_dg_cumsum_k = None\n \n     b_dk = tl.zeros([BT, BK], dtype=tl.float32)\n-    b_dv = tl.zeros([BT, BK], dtype=tl.float32)\n+    b_dv = tl.zeros([BT, BV], dtype=tl.float32)\n \n     last_chunk_start = tl.floor(i_t*BT / S).to(tl.int32) * S\n     idx_j = (tl.floor(i_t * BT / S).to(tl.int32) + 1).to(tl.int32)\n@@ -127,7 +127,7 @@ def parallel_path_bwd_dkv_kernel(\n     tl.store(p_dk, b_dk.to(dk.dtype.element_ty), boundary_check=(0, 1))\n     mask = i_t * BT + tl.arange(0, BT) < T\n     tl.atomic_add(\n-        dv + (i_t * BT + tl.arange(0, BT))[:, None] * HQ * K + tl.arange(0, BK)[None, :],\n+        dv + (i_t * BT + tl.arange(0, BT))[:, None] * HQ * V + tl.arange(0, BV)[None, :],\n         b_dv,\n         mask=mask[:, None],\n         sem='relaxed',\ndiff --git a/fla/ops/path_attn/parallel_path_bwd_inter_dqh.py b/fla/ops/path_attn/parallel_path_bwd_inter_dqh.py\nindex f1e2edf46c..608df58f1e 100644\n--- a/fla/ops/path_attn/parallel_path_bwd_inter_dqh.py\n+++ b/fla/ops/path_attn/parallel_path_bwd_inter_dqh.py\n@@ -118,9 +118,9 @@ def parallel_path_bwd_dq_kernel(\n                 b_A = b_A + b_g_cumsum_q[:, None] - b_g_cumsum_k[None, :]\n             b_A = exp2(b_A * sm_scale - b_l[:, None])\n             b_A = tl.where(m_t[:, None], b_A, 0)\n-            p_v = tl.make_block_ptr(v, (V, T), (1, V*H), (0, offset), (BK, BS), (0, 1))\n+            p_v = tl.make_block_ptr(v, (T, V), (H*V, 1), (offset, 0), (BS, BV), (1, 0))\n             b_v = tl.load(p_v, boundary_check=(0, 1))\n-            b_dp = tl.dot(b_do, b_v.to(b_do.dtype))\n+            b_dp = tl.dot(b_do, tl.trans(b_v).to(b_do.dtype))\n             b_dA = (b_dp - b_delta[:, None]) * b_A * scale\n             b_dq += tl.dot(b_dA.to(b_k.dtype), b_k)\n             if USE_GATE:\n", "test_patch": "", "problem_statement": "[Bug] Dimension mismatch in path_attn backward kernels (dkv and dqh) when K != V\n### Checklist\n\n- [x] I have checked [FAQs](https://github.com/fla-org/flash-linear-attention/blob/main/FAQs.md) and existing issues for similar problems\n- [x] Please report this bug in English to ensure wider understanding and support\n\n### Describe the Bug\n\nDuring training (specifically, during the backward pass), a `torch.distributed.elastic.multiprocessing.errors.ChildFailedError` occurs. The root cause is a dimension mismatch in the **`path_attn` Triton backward kernels**.\n\nThese kernels incorrectly assume the key dimension (`K`) and value dimension (`V`) are equal, or (more specifically) they incorrectly use `K`/`BK` constants when handling buffers and operations related to `V`/`BV`.\n\nI encountered this bug because I am **intentionally setting `BK=64` and `BV=128`** in my configuration to test the `BK != BV` scenario on my NVIDIA A6000.\n\nMy hypothesis is that this bug was likely missed during initial development because validation may have only been performed for the common case where **`BK` and `BV` are equal** (e.g., `BK=128`, `BV=128`). When `BK == BV`, the incorrect variable usage (using `BK` for a `V`-dimensioned tensor) does not cause a compilation error, thus masking the bug.\n\nThe bug reveals itself sequentially in two files as the backward pass proceeds:\n\n1.  `fla/ops/path_attn/parallel_path_bwd_inter_dkv.py`\n2.  `fla/ops/path_attn/parallel_path_bwd_inter_dqh.py`\n\n### Steps to Reproduce the Bug\n\n1.  Start training a model that uses `path_attn` on a platform where the key dimension `K` and value dimension `V` are not equal, and the auto-tuner selects differing block sizes (e.g., `BK=64`, `BV=128`).\n2.  Run the training. The process will fail during the backward pass (`loss.backward()`).\n\n-----\n\n#### Error 1: Failure in `parallel_path_bwd_inter_dkv.py`\n\nThe first error encountered is a `ValueError` during the Triton kernel compilation for `parallel_path_bwd_dkv_kernel`.\n\n**Stack Trace:**\n\n```shell\ntorch.distributed.elastic.multiprocessing.errors.ChildFailedError: \n============================================================\nflame.train FAILED\n------------------------------------------------------------\nFailures:\n\u00a0 <NO_OTHER_FAILURES>\n------------------------------------------------------------\nRoot Cause (first observed failure):\n[0]:\n\u00a0 time\u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 : 2025-11-04_09:22:44\n\u00a0 host\u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 : server\n\u00a0 rank\u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 : 1 (local_rank: 1)\n\u00a0 exitcode\u00a0 : 1 (pid: 2036851)\n\u00a0 error_file: /home/ReyJerry/flame/exp/220M_path_att_10B/logs/none_m8yqji8m/attempt_0/1/error.json\n\u00a0 traceback : Traceback (most recent call last):\n\u00a0 \u00a0 File \"/home/ReyJerry/miniconda3/envs/flame/lib/python3.13/site-packages/torch/distributed/elastic/multiprocessing/errors/__init__.py\", line 355, in wrapper\n\u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 return f(*args, **kwargs)\n\u00a0 \u00a0 File \"/home/ReyJerry/flame/flame/train.py\", line 502, in main\n\u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 loss.backward()\n\u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 ~~~~~~~~~~~~~^^\n...\n\u00a0 \u00a0 File \"/home/ReyJerry/flash-linear-attention/fla/ops/path_attn/parallel.py\", line 127, in backward\n\u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 dk, dv, _ = parallel_path_bwd_dkv_fn(\n\u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~^\n...\n\u00a0 \u00a0 File \"/home/ReyJerry/flash-linear-attention/fla/ops/path_attn/parallel_path_bwd_inter_dkv.py\", line 159, in parallel_path_bwd_dkv_fn\n\u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 parallel_path_bwd_dkv_kernel[(NT, B*HQ)](\n\u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~^\n...\n\u00a0 \u00a0 File \"/home/ReyJerry/miniconda3/envs/flame/lib/python3.13/site-packages/triton/runtime/jit.py\", line 569, in run\n\u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 kernel = self.compile(src, target=target, options=options.__dict__)\n...\n\u00a0 triton.compiler.errors.CompilationError: def parallel_path_bwd_dkv_kernel(\n...\n\u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 p_v = tl.make_block_ptr(v, (T, K), (H*K, 1), (i_t * BT, 0), (BT, BK), (1, 0))\n...\n\u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 b_dv = tl.zeros([BT, BK], dtype=tl.float32)\n...\n\u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 tl.atomic_add(\n\u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 dv + (i_t * BT + tl.arange(0, BT))[:, None] * HQ * K + tl.arange(0, BK)[None, :],\n\u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 b_dv,\n...\n\u00a0 ValueError('Cannot make_shape_compatible: incompatible dimensions at index 1: 64 and 128')\n```\n\n**Analysis 1:**\nThe kernel `parallel_path_bwd_dkv_kernel` fails compilation because it attempts to unify `K=64` and `V=128`. This is because the tensors `v` and `dv` (which have dimension `V`) are incorrectly handled using `K` or `BK` in their block pointers, shape initializations (`tl.zeros`), and `tl.atomic_add` operations.\n\n**Patch 1 (for `fla/ops/path_attn/parallel_path_bwd_inter_dkv.py`):**\nApplying the following patch fixes this specific error by changing `K`/`BK` to `V`/`BV` for `v` and `dv` operations.\n\n```diff\n@@ -82,14 +82,14 @@\n     # load query\n     p_k = tl.make_block_ptr(k, (T, K), (H*K, 1), (i_t * BT, 0), (BT, BK), (1, 0))\n     b_k = tl.load(p_k, boundary_check=(0, 1))\n-    p_v = tl.make_block_ptr(v, (T, K), (H*K, 1), (i_t * BT, 0), (BT, BK), (1, 0))\n+    # v's second dimension is V, not K\n+    p_v = tl.make_block_ptr(v, (T, V), (H*V, 1), (i_t * BT, 0), (BT, BV), (1, 0))\n     b_v = tl.load(p_v, boundary_check=(0, 1))\n \n     if USE_GATE:\n@@ -102,7 +102,8 @@\n         b_dg_cumsum_k = None\n \n     b_dk = tl.zeros([BT, BK], dtype=tl.float32)\n-    b_dv = tl.zeros([BT, BK], dtype=tl.float32)\n+    # dv has the same width as v: BV\n+    b_dv = tl.zeros([BT, BV], dtype=tl.float32)\n \n     last_chunk_start = tl.floor(i_t*BT / S).to(tl.int32) * S\n     idx_j = (tl.floor(i_t * BT / S).to(tl.int32) + 1).to(tl.int32)\n@@ -137,13 +138,13 @@\n     p_dk = tl.make_block_ptr(dk, (T, K), (HQ*K, 1), (i_t * BT, 0), (BT, BK), (1, 0))\n     tl.store(p_dk, b_dk.to(dk.dtype.element_ty), boundary_check=(0, 1))\n     mask = i_t * BT + tl.arange(0, BT) < T\n+    # dv's row stride is HQ*V, and its block width is BV\n     tl.atomic_add(\n-        dv + (i_t * BT + tl.arange(0, BT))[:, None] * HQ * K + tl.arange(0, BK)[None, :],\n+        dv + (i_t * BT + tl.arange(0, BT))[:, None] * HQ * V + tl.arange(0, BV)[None, :],\n         b_dv,\n         mask=mask[:, None],\n         sem='relaxed'\n     )\n     if USE_GATE:\n         tl.atomic_add(dg_cumsum + (i_t * BT + tl.arange(0, BT)) * HQ, b_dg_cumsum_k, mask=mask, sem='relaxed')\n\n```\n\n-----\n\n#### Error 2: Failure in `parallel_path_bwd_inter_dqh.py`\n\n3.  After applying **Patch 1**, restart the training.\n4.  The training will fail during the backward pass again, this time with an `AssertionError` in `parallel_path_bwd_dq_kernel`.\n\n**Stack Trace:**\n\n```shell\ntorch.distributed.elastic.multiprocessing.errors.ChildFailedError: \n============================================================\nflame.train FAILED\n------------------------------------------------------------\nFailures:\n\u00a0 <NO_OTHER_FAILURES>\n------------------------------------------------------------\nRoot Cause (first observed failure):\n[0]:\n\u00a0 time\u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 : 2025-11-04_09:32:19\n\u00a0 host\u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 : server\n\u00a0 rank\u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 : 1 (local_rank: 1)\n\u00a0 exitcode\u00a0 : 1 (pid: 2046766)\n\u00a0 error_file: /home/ReyJerry/flame/exp/220M_path_att_10B/logs/none_n9_1xtcz/attempt_0/1/error.json\n\u00a0 traceback : Traceback (most recent call last):\n\u00a0 \u00a0 File \"/home/ReyJerry/miniconda3/envs/flame/lib/python3.13/site-packages/triton/language/core.py\", line 34, in wrapper\n\u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 return fn(*args, **kwargs)\n\u00a0 \u00a0 File \"/home/ReyJerry/miniconda3/envs/flame/lib/python3.13/site-packages/triton/language/core.py\", line 1814, in dot\n\u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 return semantic.dot(input, other, acc, input_precision, max_num_imprecise_acc, out_dtype, _builder)\n\u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0~~~~~~~~~~~~^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^\n\u00a0 \u00a0 File \"/home/ReyJerry/miniconda3/envs/flame/lib/python3.13/site-packages/triton/language/semantic.py\", line 1566, in dot\n\u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 assert lhs.shape[-1].value == rhs.shape[\n\u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^\n\u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 -2].value, f\"First input shape ({lhs.shape}) and second input shape {rhs.shape} are not compatible for matmul (second index of first shape ({lhs.shape[-1].value}) must be equal to first index of second shape ({rhs.shape[-2].value})\"\n\u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 ^^^^^^^^^\n\u00a0 AssertionError: First input shape (['constexpr[64]', 'constexpr[128]']) and second input shape ['constexpr[64]', 'constexpr[32]'] are not compatible for matmul (second index of first shape (128) must be equal to first index of second shape (64)\n...\n\u00a0 \u00a0 File \"/home/ReyJerry/flash-linear-attention/fla/ops/path_attn/parallel.py\", line 144, in backward\n\u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 dq, dhc_whole, dg_cumsum = parallel_path_bwd_dq_fn(\n\u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~^\n...\n\u00a0 \u00a0 File \"/home/ReyJerry/flash-linear-attention/fla/ops/path_attn/parallel_path_bwd_inter_dqh.py\", line 169, in parallel_path_bwd_dq_fn\n\u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 parallel_path_bwd_dq_kernel[(NT, B*HQ)](\n\u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~^\n...\n\u00a0 triton.compiler.errors.CompilationError: at 109:19:\n\u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 ...\n\u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 p_v = tl.make_block_ptr(v, (V, T), (1, V*H), (0, offset), (BK, BS), (0, 1))\n\u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 b_v = tl.load(p_v, boundary_check=(0, 1))\n\u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 b_dp = tl.dot(b_do, b_v.to(b_do.dtype))\n\u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0^\n```\n\n**Analysis 2:**\nThe kernel `parallel_path_bwd_dq_kernel` is attempting to compute `dP = dO @ V^T`.\n\n  * `b_do` has shape `[BS, BV]` (e.g., `[64, 128]` based on the assertion).\n  * The kernel incorrectly loads `v` using a `(V, T)` layout and a `(BK, BS)` block size (e.g., `[64, 32]`, as inferred from the assertion failure).\n  * The `tl.dot(b_do, b_v)` operation fails because the shapes are incompatible for matrix multiplication (`[BS, BV] @ [BK, BS]`).\n  * The correct operation should be `tl.dot(b_do, tl.trans(b_v))`, with `b_v` loaded as `[BS, BV]`.\n\n**Patch 2 (for `fla/ops/path_attn/parallel_path_bwd_inter_dqh.py`):**\nApplying the following patch fixes this second error by correcting the `v` tensor's loading layout, block size, and applying the necessary transpose in the dot product.\n\n```diff\n@@ -106,9 +106,10 @@\n                 b_g_cumsum_k = tl.load(p_g_cumsum_k, boundary_check=(0,)).to(tl.float32)\n                 b_A = b_A + b_g_cumsum_q[:, None] - b_g_cumsum_k[None, :]\n             b_A = exp2(b_A * sm_scale - b_l[:, None])\n             b_A = tl.where(m_t[:, None], b_A, 0)\n-            p_v = tl.make_block_ptr(v, (V, T), (1, V*H), (0, offset), (BK, BS), (0, 1))\n+            # V should be read as (T, V) with block size (BS, BV) for dP = dO @ V^T\n+            p_v = tl.make_block_ptr(v, (T, V), (H*V, 1), (offset, 0), (BS, BV), (1, 0))\n             b_v = tl.load(p_v, boundary_check=(0, 1))\n-            b_dp = tl.dot(b_do, b_v.to(b_do.dtype))\n+            b_dp = tl.dot(b_do, tl.trans(b_v).to(b_do.dtype))\n \n             if USE_GATE:\n                 b_dA = (b_dp * scale * b_A)\n```\n\n### Expected Behavior\n\nTraining should complete successfully without any ValueError or AssertionError, even when the key dimension (K) and value dimension (V) are different. The Triton kernels in path_attn should correctly handle v and dv tensors using their proper V and BV dimensions, strides, and block sizes, rather than incorrectly using K and BK.\n\n### Environment Information\n\n1. Platform/GPU: NVIDIA A6000 \n2. Torch: 3.13\n3. Triton: 3.3.0\n", "hints_text": "\n\n", "all_hints_text": "wow, thanks you so much!! will fix it soon\n> wow, thanks you so much!! will fix it soon\n\nYou're welcome~ Following up on the issue I reported (Issue #632), I've just submitted two Pull Requests with the code fixes. I hope this contribution is helpful and can be accepted. Please let me know if any changes are needed.\n\n", "commit_urls": ["https://github.com/fla-org/flash-linear-attention/commit/4af0f80259c534180175601667f95e4228f11dcc", "https://github.com/fla-org/flash-linear-attention/commit/1dde16f8e864fe509cdbfff7dbe35a3d77669aec"], "created_at": "2025-11-05T17:56:23Z"}
{"repo": "fla-org/flash-linear-attention", "pull_number": 687, "instance_id": "fla-org__flash-linear-attention-687", "issue_numbers": [638], "base_commit": "c9de46182edbe9929de773b39cc6aee0bb481365", "patch": "diff --git a/fla/ops/gated_delta_rule/wy_fast.py b/fla/ops/gated_delta_rule/wy_fast.py\nindex c5119dcf7c..f727880a49 100644\n--- a/fla/ops/gated_delta_rule/wy_fast.py\n+++ b/fla/ops/gated_delta_rule/wy_fast.py\n@@ -7,7 +7,33 @@\n \n from fla.ops.utils import prepare_chunk_indices\n from fla.ops.utils.op import exp\n-from fla.utils import autotune_cache_kwargs, check_shared_mem\n+from fla.utils import IS_NVIDIA_BLACKWELL, autotune_cache_kwargs, check_shared_mem\n+\n+if IS_NVIDIA_BLACKWELL:\n+    \"\"\"\n+    Compute tl.dot with SM100 workaround.\n+\n+    On SM100 (Blackwell) GPUs, wraps the result in inline assembly to prevent\n+    the TritonGPUHoistTMEMAlloc pass from incorrectly fusing add and dot operations.\n+    See: https://github.com/fla-org/flash-linear-attention/issues/638\n+\n+    TODO: Remove this workaround once the Triton compiler bug is fixed.\n+    Track upstream issue at: https://github.com/triton-lang/triton/issues/8695\n+    \"\"\"\n+    @triton.jit\n+    def safe_dot(a, b):\n+        return tl.inline_asm_elementwise(\n+            asm=\"mov.f32 $0, $1;\",\n+            constraints=\"=r,r\",\n+            args=[tl.dot(a, b)],\n+            dtype=tl.float32,\n+            is_pure=True,\n+            pack=1,\n+        )\n+else:\n+    @triton.jit\n+    def safe_dot(a, b):\n+        return tl.dot(a, b)\n \n \n @triton.heuristics({\n@@ -198,7 +224,7 @@ def prepare_wy_repr_bwd_kernel(\n         b_A += tl.dot(b_kb, tl.trans(b_k))\n         b_dkb = tl.dot(b_dA, b_k)\n         b_db += tl.sum(b_dkb * b_k, 1)\n-        b_dk += tl.dot(tl.trans(b_dA), b_kb)\n+        b_dk += safe_dot(tl.trans(b_dA), b_kb)\n         b_dk += b_dkb * b_b[:, None]\n         tl.store(p_dk, b_dk.to(p_dk.dtype.element_ty), boundary_check=(0, 1))\n     tl.store(p_db, b_db.to(p_db.dtype.element_ty), boundary_check=(0,))\ndiff --git a/fla/utils.py b/fla/utils.py\nindex af9658aa00..f472f11bc3 100644\n--- a/fla/utils.py\n+++ b/fla/utils.py\n@@ -395,6 +395,7 @@ def map_triton_backend_to_torch_device() -> str:\n IS_NVIDIA = (device_platform == 'cuda')\n IS_INTEL_ALCHEMIST = (IS_INTEL and 'Intel(R) Arc(TM) A' in torch.xpu.get_device_name(0))\n IS_NVIDIA_HOPPER = (IS_NVIDIA and ('NVIDIA H' in torch.cuda.get_device_name(0) or torch.cuda.get_device_capability()[0] >= 9))\n+IS_NVIDIA_BLACKWELL = (IS_NVIDIA and torch.cuda.get_device_capability()[0] == 10)\n USE_CUDA_GRAPH = (IS_NVIDIA and os.environ.get('FLA_USE_CUDA_GRAPH', '0') == '1')\n \n # Nvidia Ampere or newer, haven't check AMD and intel yet.\n@@ -477,6 +478,7 @@ def _register_aliases():\n         'IS_NVIDIA',\n         'IS_INTEL_ALCHEMIST',\n         'IS_NVIDIA_HOPPER',\n+        'IS_NVIDIA_BLACKWELL',\n         'USE_CUDA_GRAPH',\n         'IS_TF32_SUPPORTED',\n         'IS_GATHER_SUPPORTED',\n", "test_patch": "", "problem_statement": "[Bug] GatedDeltaNet backward error on Blackwell: 'error: operand #2 does not dominate this use'\n### Checklist\n\n- [x] I have checked [FAQs](https://github.com/fla-org/flash-linear-attention/blob/main/FAQs.md) and existing issues for similar problems\n- [x] Please report this bug in English to ensure wider understanding and support\n\n### Describe the Bug\n\nWhen executing GDN backwards on Blackwell triton 3.5.0, the following error happens. \n\n```\nflash-linear-attention/fla/ops/gated_delta_rule/chunk.py:331: UserWarning: head_first is deprecated and will be removed in a future version. Please use head_first=False for now instead.\n  warnings.warn(\nflash-linear-attention/fla/ops/gated_delta_rule/chunk.py:331: UserWarning: head_first is deprecated and will be removed in a future version. Please use head_first=False for now instead.\n  warnings.warn(\nflash-linear-attention/fla/ops/gated_delta_rule/wy_fast.py:208:39: error: operand #2 does not dominate this use\n        b_dk += tl.dot(tl.trans(b_dA), b_kb)\n                                      ^\nflash-linear-attention/fla/ops/gated_delta_rule/wy_fast.py:208:16: note: operand defined here (op in the same block)\n        b_dk += tl.dot(tl.trans(b_dA), b_kb)\n               ^\nmodule {\n  tt.func public @prepare_wy_repr_bwd_kernel(%arg0: !tt.ptr<bf16> {tt.divisibility = 16 : i32}, %arg1: !tt.ptr<bf16> {tt.divisibility = 16 : i32}, %arg2: !tt.ptr<f32> {tt.divisibility = 16 : i32}, %arg3: !tt.ptr<f32> {tt.divisibility = 16 : i32}, %arg4: !tt.ptr<bf16> {tt.divisibility = 16 : i32}, %arg5: !tt.ptr<bf16> {tt.divisibility = 16 : i32}, %arg6: !tt.ptr<bf16> {tt.divisibility = 16 : i32}, %arg7: !tt.ptr<bf16> {tt.divisibility = 16 : i32}, %arg8: !tt.ptr<bf16> {tt.divisibility = 16 : i32}, %arg9: !tt.ptr<f32> {tt.divisibility = 16 : i32}, %arg10: !tt.ptr<f32> {tt.divisibility = 16 : i32}, %arg11: !tt.ptr<bf16> {tt.divisibility = 16 : i32}, %arg12: !tt.ptr<f32> {tt.divisibility = 16 : i32}, %arg13: i32) attributes {noinline = false} {\n    %cst = arith.constant dense<128> : tensor<1x64xi64>\n    %cst_0 = arith.constant dense<4096> : tensor<64x1xi64>\n    %cst_1 = arith.constant dense<0> : tensor<1x64xi64>\n    %cst_2 = arith.constant dense<64> : tensor<64x1xi64>\n    %cst_3 = arith.constant dense<0> : tensor<64x1xi64>\n    %cst_4 = arith.constant dense<2048> : tensor<1x64xi64>\n    %cst_5 = arith.constant dense<0> : tensor<64xi64>\n    %cst_6 = arith.constant dense<32> : tensor<64xi64>\n    %c2_i32 = arith.constant 2 : i32\n    %cst_7 = arith.constant dense<0.000000e+00> : tensor<64xf32>\n    %c1_i32 = arith.constant 1 : i32\n    %cst_8 = arith.constant dense<0.000000e+00> : tensor<64x64xf32>\n    %c128_i32 = arith.constant 128 : i32\n    %c0_i32 = arith.constant 0 : i32\n    %c64_i32 = arith.constant 64 : i32\n    %c32_i32 = arith.constant 32 : i32\n    %0 = tt.get_program_id x : i32\n    %1 = tt.get_program_id y : i32\n    %2 = arith.divsi %1, %c32_i32 : i32\n    %3 = arith.remsi %